main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Duluth, Minnesota on April 2, 1965, where an object was seen maneuvering erratically for approximately 30 minutes.
interesting points: The sighting was reported by pilots who observed the object from F-89 aircraft., The object was described as round, basketball-sized, and white., Both pilots mentioned the weather conditions were VFR (Visual Flight Rules)., A balloon was released by the St. Cloud and Minneapolis weather stations during the time of the sighting., The conclusion drawn from the report suggested that the object could have been a balloon reflecting sunlight.
witness description: pilots from the 179th Air National Guard Fighter Wing
